#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "Performance Settings"
msgstr "Nastavitve delovanja"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&konqueror; is used on a wide variety of computers by a wide variety of "
"users. Under the category of performance, this dialog allows each user to "
"adjust options which may make the computer that &konqueror; is installed on "
"feel more responsive."
msgstr ""
"&konqueror; se uporablja na najrazličnejših računalnikih s strani "
"najrazličnejših uporabnikov. Pod kategorijo zmogljivosti to pogovorno okno "
"omogoča vsakemu uporabniku, da prilagodi možnosti, zaradi katerih je lahko "
"&konqueror; na računalniku kjer nameščen, na občutek bolj odziven."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Preloading"
msgstr "Prednalaganje"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The subsection labeled <guilabel>Preloading</guilabel> makes a tradeoff "
"between memory and performance."
msgstr ""
"Pododdelek z oznako <guilabel>Prednalaganje</guilabel> naredi kompromis med "
"pomnilnikom in zmogljivostjo."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Preloading</emphasis> refers to loading an instance of &konqueror; "
"into memory before a user asks to start &konqueror;. The positive effect of "
"this is that when a user asks to load &konqueror; the window appears "
"instantly because most of the application has been preloaded. The negative "
"effect is that this instance of &konqueror; uses memory that could be used "
"by other programs. By default, when a user closes &konqueror;, the instance "
"is not closed. This means that the next time a user wants &konqueror; "
"loaded, it is nearly instantaneous again."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis>Prednalaganje</emphasis> se nanaša na nalaganje primerka "
"&konqueror; v pomnilnik, preden uporabnik zahteva zagon &konqueror;. "
"Pozitivni učinek tega je, da ko uporabnik zahteva nalaganje &konqueror; okno "
"se prikaže takoj, ker je večina aplikacije vnaprej naložena. Negativni "
"učinek je, da ta primerek &konqueror; uporablja pomnilnik, ki bi ga lahko "
"uporabljali drugi programi. Privzeto, ko uporabnik zapre &konqueror;, "
"primerek ni zaprt. To pomeni, da naslednjič, ko uporabnik želi &konqueror; "
"naložen, je spet skoraj v trenutku."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The final check box labeled <guilabel>Always try to have at least one "
"preloaded instance</guilabel> signals that you always want to have one "
"preloaded, but not used, instance of &konqueror; available. This option will "
"actually decrease performance on some machines (especially those with "
"limited physical memory)."
msgstr ""
"Zadnje potrditveno polje z oznako <guilabel>Vedno poskušaj imeti vsaj en "
"prednaložen primerek</guilabel> pomeni, da vedno želiš imeti en prednaložen, "
"a neuporabljen primerek &konqueror; na voljo. Ta možnost bo dejansko "
"zmanjšala zmogljivost nekaterih strojev (zlasti tistih z omejenim fizičnim "
"pomnilnikom)."

